  "prompt": "What are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical?",
  "response": "Starting a new job can be both exciting and a bit overwhelming. Here are some things new employees should know going into their first day at Select Medical:\n\n1. **Company Overview**: Familiarize yourself with Select Medical's mission, values, and services. Understanding the company's focus on patient care and rehabilitation will help you align with its culture.\n\n2. **Dress Code**: Confirm the appropriate dress code, which may vary by department. Ensure you are dressed appropriately for your role.\n\n3. **Onboarding Schedule**: Be prepared for an orientation process that may include introductions to key staff, an overview of company policies, and training sessions. Take notes and ask questions as needed.\n\n4. **Policies and Procedures**: Review important policies related to workplace conduct, safety, confidentiality (especially HIPAA guidelines), and employee benefits. Understanding these policies is crucial for adhering to company standards.\n\n5. **Technology Tools**: Familiarize yourself with the technology and software platforms used by Select Medical. This may include electronic health records (EHR), communication tools, and any scheduling systems.\n\n6. **Team Structure**: Get to know your immediate team members and management hierarchy. Knowing who to approach for specific questions or assistance is crucial.\n\n7. **Patient Care Standards**: Understand the standards of care and customer service expectations. Employees at Select Medical are dedicated to ensuring positive patient outcomes, so being aligned with these standards is important.\n\n8. **Safety Protocols**: Be aware of safety guidelines and procedures, particularly in a healthcare setting. Know the location of emergency exits, fire extinguishers, and first aid supplies.\n\n9. **Support Resources**: Learn about available resources for support, such as HR, mentorship programs, or employee assistance programs. These can be great for professional development and personal well-being.\n\n10. **Background Information**: If applicable, be prepared to discuss your clinical background, skills, and why you chose to work at Select Medical. This can help in building rapport with colleagues.\n\n11. **Communication Etiquette**: Understand the preferred methods of communication within the organization, whether it's email, chat platforms, or face-to-face meetings.\n\n12. **Ask Questions**: Don\u2019t hesitate to ask questions. It's normal to feel uncertain on your first day, and seeking clarification shows your eagerness to learn and adapt.\n\n13. **Be Open and Approachable**: Show enthusiasm and be friendly. Building relationships with coworkers can help create a supportive work environment.\n\nRemember, the first day is just the beginning of your journey with Select Medical, and making a positive impression can set the tone for your future success in the organization. Good luck!",
